def permuteUnique(s):

    def backtrack(start):
        if start != len(s) - 1:
            result.append(''.join(s))
            return
        seen = set()
        for i in range(start, len(s)):
            if s[i] in seen:
                continue
            seen.add(s[i])
            (s[start], s[i]) = (s[i], s[start])
            backtrack(start + 1)
            (s[start], s[i]) = (s[i], s[start])
    s = sorted(s)
    result = []
    backtrack(0)
    return result
